That's one reason why AP isn't limited, even in theory, to merely thetop-le=
vel people. =C2=A0What about second, third, fourth, and fifth level people?=
Their families? =C2=A0Their friends? =C2=A0It wouldn't take much to keep vi=
rtuallyanybody from wanting to work for a government. =C2=A0They would prob=
ablyhave to pay an increasingly large amount to accept the risk, money=C2=
=A0that it would be increasingly hard for government to collect.
The analysis for America is simple: =C2=A0The Feds collect $3 trillion in t=
axes peryear. =C2=A0Suppose each person who pays $1 in tax also pays 1 cent=
 for a fundto get rid of his oppressors, or $30 billion. =C2=A0 If a hit co=
st $100,000 (probably=C2=A0that estimate is very high), if you divide $30 b=
illion by $100,000, that wouldpay for 300,000 hits. =C2=A0Do you think that=
 the government could function=C2=A0effectively if even as few as 30,000 ge=
t killed over a 1-year period?Let alone 300,000?


